<h3 style="text-align:left"> FEATURES: </h3> <u1 style="text-align:left;font family:roman;fontsize:40px">
<li>The horse is a domesticated, one-toed, hoofed mammal.</li>
<li>It belongs to the taxonomic family Equidae and is one of two extant subspecies of Equus ferus.</li>
<li>The horse has evolved over the past 45 to 55 million years from a small multi-toed creature, Eohippus, into the large, single-toed animal of today.</li>
<li>Horses and other animals were used to pull wheeled vehicles, chariots, carts and wagons and horses were increasingly used for riding in the Near East from at least c. 2000 BC onwards. </li>
<li>Horses were used in war, in hunting and as a means of transport.</li>
